:: kidKgate2
Both of you are going to create sparks. To play a spark, imagine a bright light that quickly disappears, and play a quick note on the piano. Make sure to share the piano! Perhaps, one of you can take the black keys, and the other can take the white keys.

<<linkreplace "Tap to continue." t8n>>
When you can both do sparks, try adding some flames into the mix. To play a flame, just find any two keys with one white key between them, and play them back and forth, over and over. 
<<linkreplace "Tap to continue." t8n>>
Play a game where if one of you plays a spark, the other should respond with a flame near that same place. If you lose track of the last spark your partner did, just wait for the next one. 

You can try to catch each other out, but don’t try to win. Just have fun and work together. Try and keep the music going without stopping.

When you’re happy with how sparks and flames work, tap ‘Next’.
